  "docs": {
    "sections": [
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Draw samples from a standard Cauchy distribution with mode = 0."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Summary"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Also known as the Lorentz distribution."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Extended Summary"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "Output shape.  If the given shape is, e.g., "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "(m, n, k)"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": ", then\n"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "m * n * k"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " samples are drawn.  Default is None, in which case a\nsingle value is returned."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "int or tuple of ints, optional",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "Output shape.  If the given shape is, e.g., "
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "code",
                    "text": "(m, n, k)"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": ", then\n"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "code",
                    "text": "m * n * k"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": " samples are drawn.  Default is None, in which case a\nsingle value is returned."
                  }
                ],
                "name": "size",
                "type": "field_list"
              }
            ],
            "title": "Parameters",
            "type": "field_list"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Parameters"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "The drawn samples."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "ndarray or scalar",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "The drawn samples."
                  }
                ],
                "name": "samples",
                "type": "field_list"
              }
            ],
            "title": "Returns",
            "type": "field_list"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Returns"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The probability density function for the full Cauchy distribution is"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "formulas": [
              "P(x; x_0, \\gamma) = \\frac{1}{\\pi \\gamma \\bigl[ 1+ (\\frac{x-x_0}{\\gamma})^2 \\bigr] }"
            ],
            "type": "math_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "and the Standard Cauchy distribution just sets "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "x_0=0"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " and\n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "\\gamma=1"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The Cauchy distribution arises in the solution to the driven harmonic\noscillator problem, and also describes spectral line broadening. It\nalso describes the distribution of values at which a line tilted at\na random angle will cut the x axis."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "When studying hypothesis tests that assume normality, seeing how the\ntests perform on data from a Cauchy distribution is a good indicator of\ntheir sensitivity to a heavy-tailed distribution, since the Cauchy looks\nvery much like a Gaussian distribution, but with heavier tails."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Notes"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "1\n\nNIST/SEMATECH e-Handbook of Statistical Methods, \"Cauchy\nDistribution\",\nhttps://www.itl.nist.gov/div898/handbook/eda/section3/eda3663.htm",
            "type": "raw_block"
          },
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "2\n\nWeisstein, Eric W. \"Cauchy Distribution.\" From MathWorld--A\nWolfram Web Resource.\nhttps://mathworld.wolfram.com/CauchyDistribution.html",
            "type": "raw_block"
          },
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "3\n\nWikipedia, \"Cauchy distribution\"\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cauchy_distribution",
            "type": "raw_block"
          }
        ],
        "title": "References"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Draw samples and plot the distribution:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "rng = flops.random.default_rng()"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "s = rng.standard_cauchy(1000000)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "s = s[(s>-25) & (s<25)]  # truncate distribution so it plots well"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "plt.hist(s, bins=100)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "plt.show()"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Examples"
      }
    ]
  },
